The reference sequence used for comparison of the ArkGA passages was the full genome of the Ark99 pathogenic field virus (unpublished sequence). In the ArkGA P1 vaccine consensus sequence, mutations occurred in polyprotein 1a, the spike gene, and in a non-coding region (Fig. 1
). Only the mutation occurring in the spike gene resulted in an amino acid change (Table 1
).
